definition: can/may/able to/to approve/to permit/to suit/(particle used for emphasis) certainly/very
decline to comment/not express an opinion/be noncommittal/hedge
to refuse to comment/same as 不置可否

sentences.english: Can I manage to make it back in one piece?
sentences.chinese: 我可否設法把它一次搬回來？

sentences.english: There is no denying, that as a challenger now, we have a fight on our hands.
sentences.chinese: 不可否認，我們作爲挑戰者，將有一場硬仗要打。

sentences.english: However, whether retenes can be derived from lower organisms, such as algae is not confirmed so far.
sentences.chinese: 但藻類等低等生物可否形成惹烯卻未被證實。

sentences.english: Of course, what goes up must come down.
sentences.chinese: 當然，不可否認的是，跳上去就必定得落下來。

sentences.english: Can non-national public servants commit the bribery crime?
sentences.chinese: 非國家工作人員可否構成受賄罪共犯？

sentences.english: Can we have permission to start-up left outboard for engine check Stand B14.
sentences.chinese: 可否允許啓動左側發動機檢查，現停在B14號位置。

sentences.english: Will the first to use contraceptives, "Yasmin", can reduce the dose of their own?
sentences.chinese: 請問初次用避孕藥“優思明”，可否自行減小劑量？

sentences.english: And can we learn anything about human sexual behaviour from all this?
sentences.chinese: 那麼我們人類可否從這些動物的性行爲中學到什麼呢？

sentences.english: But there's no denying how world-changing those inventions were.
sentences.chinese: 但是不可否認，世界因爲這些創新而改變。

sentences.english: Two sentences, admittedly, but what a pair.
sentences.chinese: 兩個句子，無可否認的，真成對。

sentences.english: What was your overseas exchange experience like?
sentences.chinese: 可否分享海外交流經驗？

sentences.english: Responsibility is the ruler, can measure.
sentences.chinese: 責任是標尺，丈量可否行。

sentences.english: Are you worrying about the non-execution of the contract and non-payment on our part?
sentences.chinese: 你可否憂鬱我們不履行合同或者拒不付款？

sentences.english: Yes, there have been differences between America and Europe.
sentences.chinese: 不可否認，歐美之間已存在分歧。

sentences.english: I doubt he misses me after our last meeting.
sentences.chinese: 不知上次一別之後他可否想念我。
電子銀行交易的不可否認與可追查責任特性。

definition: how about it?/what do you think?
(courteous) to be so bold as to
to come with a specific purpose in mind
brother (polite appellation for a friend one's age)
to hinder/(in the negative or interrogative) (no) harm/(what) harm
you all (archaic)/see also 你們|你们[ni3 men5]
